						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Pillar in Karīmuddīn's Mosque.</hi></p>						

						<p>Kannara—A.D. 1256-57.</p>						

						<p>This inscription refers to the reign of <hi rend="bold">Kanharadēva</hi> and is dated in <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1179, Naḷa.</hi> Further details are not given. The Śaka year given is the current year The cyclic year <hi rend="bold">Naḷa</hi> corresponds to <hi rend="bold">A.D. 1256-57.</hi></p>						

						<p>It records a grant of land made to a certain <hi rend="bold">Rāmōja</hi> by <hi rend="italic">āchārya</hi> <hi rend="bold">Lōkarāsidēva</hi></p>						

						</summary>
